        <Parent_String>construction workers [300025001], people in engineering, building trades and planning [300168334], people by occupation [300024980], people (agents) [300024979], People (hierarchy name) [300024978], Agents Facet [300264089]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Those who build with wood, especially in the construction of buildings and other structures, including the installation of floors, windows, and other trim work. For craftsmen who make fine furniture and do intricate woodwork, see "cabinetmakers." For those who work in wood more generally, see "woodworkers."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079228/Grove Art Online (2008-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Aquellos que trabajan la madera, especialmente para construcción de edificios y otras estructuras, incluyendo la instalación de pisos, ventanas, y otros trabajos de especial cuidado. Para artesanos que fabrican muebles finos y hacen artesanías complejas, en madera, ver "ebanista.” Para los que trabajan en madera más generalizada, ver los "tallista de madera.”</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Personen die gebouwen en andere houten constructies in hout optrekken, en ook vloeren, ramen en kozijnen installeren. Zie 'kastenmakers' voor vakmensen die verfijnde meubels en ingewikkeld houtwerk vervaardigen. Zie 'houtbewerkers' voor mensen die in algemene zin hout bewerken.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>以木材建造建築物或其他結構者，亦可指鋪設地板、裝置窗框和進行細部刨整工作者。製作高級家具和從事精細木工之工匠，參見「細木工」。而「木工」一詞則可泛指從事木工相關行業者。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
